  "abstract": "Photoperiod-sensitive flowering is a key adaptive trait for sorghum (Sorghum bicolor) in\r\nWest and Central Africa. In this study we performed an association analysis to investigate the\r\neffect of polymorphisms within the genes putatively related to variation in flowering time on\r\nphotoperiod-sensitive flowering in sorghum. For this purpose a genetically characterized\r\npanel of 219 sorghum accessions from West and Central Africa was evaluated for their\r\nphotoperiod response index (PRI) based on two sowing dates under field conditions.",
